title: The Inevitability of Destructive Intelligence
description:
An argument for the position that in any world with scarcity, variability, and competition, advanced intelligence will reliably evolve into a force that restructures or destroys weaker systems as a byproduct of securing its own persistence.
- Tyler Vinson
